in Dante's view).  It seems possible, however, that Dante is willing to
allow the philosopher himself a potential escape route; he may have seemed
to him, in the end, more like a poet than a philosopher" (Hollander). Il
comm. di Bosco-Reggio cos@i recita: "La teoria dell'origine dell'anima
